name: 16-methyl-17-oxoandrost-5-en-3-yl acetate
source: Karthikeyan M.; Glen R.C.; Bender A. General melting point prediction based on a diverse compound dataset and artificial neural networks. J. Chem. Inf. Model.; 2005; 45(3); 581-3550
Reason:
16-methyl-17-oxoandrost-5-en-3-yl acetate has a melting point that can be predicted by considering its structural components. The basic unit for comparison is 1-methylcyclohexane, which has a melting point of 10.5°C. The functional groups present in 16-methyl-17-oxoandrost-5-en-3-yl acetate include a methyl group, a phenyl group, a carboxyl group, and an oxo group. Each of these groups can contribute to the melting point in different ways:
* Methyl group: +5°C (increased molecular weight and rigidity)
* Phenyl group: +20°C (increased molecular weight and rigidity, as well as potential hydrogen bonding)
* Carboxyl group: +5°C (increased molecular weight and rigidity)
* Oxo group: +10°C (increased molecular weight and rigidity, as well as potential hydrogen bonding)
* The methyl group and phenyl group contribute more significantly to the melting point due to their ability to enhance molecular rigidity and pi-pi interactions. The carboxyl group and oxo group contribute less due to their smaller size and lower potential for hydrogen bonding.
